-- UBS Hires Citigroup's Revsine as U.S. Derivatives Strategist in New York
-- Jeff Kearns
-- 2010-07-13T15:11:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/ubs-hires-citigroup-s-revsine-as-u-s-derivatives-strategist-in-new-york.html

          
          
             UBS AG hired  Mitchell Revsine , an
options strategist from Citigroup Inc., as the U.S. derivatives
strategist in New York.  
 Revsine, 43, will work with stock analysts to produce 
reports about the options market and trade recommendations, 
according to a memo sent to UBS employees today. He will be an 
executive director and will report to  David Bleustein , head 
of U.S. equities research, the memo said.  
 Revsine spent the past three years as an equity derivatives
strategist at Citigroup in New York and has worked in the
industry for 15 years, according to the memo, which was
confirmed by UBS spokeswoman  Allison Chin-Leong . Revsine
previously worked at Merrill Lynch & Co. for three years and
spent seven years at JPMorgan Chase & Co., according to
Financial Industry Regulatory Authority  records .  
 UBS, based in Zurich, is the biggest Swiss bank.  
